veloped and delivery commenced in January with Corporate Induction. Plan to put into an online format and roll out to existing employees throughout the year. Investigation into online training platforms underway.','1','LA3.1.7'),(0000000716,NULL,'16/17',01,60,'Work continues with the development of the High Performance Booster framework and development program for leadership team. Implementation to commence February 2017.','1','LA3.3.10'),(0000000717,NULL,'16/17',01,65,'Gaps are being covered by the use of SharePoint and spreadsheets in the interim until the Corporate Information System project is completed. New systems may be introduced through this process. Work has commenced on expanding existing competency system OO-Soft to better manage and report on organisational training information. A trial of this is to commence in March 2017.','1','LA3.3.12'),(0000000718,NULL,'16/17',01,0,'Planned commencement in March 2017.','2','LA3.3.14'),(0000000719,NULL,'16/17',01,0,'Investigation and scoping to commence March 2017.','2','LA3.3.20'),(0000000720,NULL,'16/17',01,65,'Policy, procedure and forms reviewed. A review of the induction process has commenced. Investigating opportunities for greater volunteer participation in the delivery of Library Services.','1','LA3.3.23'),(0000000721,NULL,'16/17',01,20,'Review has commenced. Draft plan scheduled ','1','LA3.8.2'),(0000000722,NULL,'16/17',01,10,'1. Council has resolved to accept a tender to install street lighting in a Centre Median in Maitland Street. Centre median design including street trees currently being finalised to seek quotes. 2. Pedestrian refuges on Tibbereena Street/Highway fully funded by Roads and Maritime Services and currently being designed. 3. Some new seats installed in CBD. ','3','OC1.2.3'),(0000000723,NULL,'16/17',01,75,'Public swimming pool operating hours reviewed in August 2016 for summer season 2016/2017 to meet objective of maximum subsidy of $15 per user/per use. Winter swimming pool operating hours for the Narrabri Aquatic Centre currently under development taking into consideration requests and feedback from the community. ','1','OC3.2.3'),(0000000724,NULL,'16/17',01,80,'Draft report recieved on Structural Integrity and Remaining Life of Assets for Public Swimming Pools in Narrabri Shire. Draft report has been reviewed and consultants instructed to finalise report. Some recommendations of the draft report have been incorporated into budget requests for 2017/2018 for Council\'s consideration. ','1','OC3.2.10'),(0000000725,NULL,'16/17',01,80,'Draft Levels of Service and Maintenance Standards currently implemented with monitoring and improvement occurring regularly to identify savings. Further detailed inspection is expected as part of Efficiency Review process. ','1','OC6.12.1'),(0000000726,NULL,'16/17',01,50,'Narrabri Shire Sport, Recreation and Open Space Plan commissioned including the requirement to develop a prioritised list of Crown Land requiring Plans of Management. Community consultation to assist develop the draft Sport, Recreation and Open Space Plan was deliberately delayed due to planned extensive community consultation relating to the Community Strategic Plan and Disability Inclusion Action Plan (DIAP). The draft Sport and Recreation Plan is now expected by end April 2017. ','3','OC6.12.3'),(0000000727,NULL,'16/17',01,50,'Narrabri Shire Sport and Recreation Plan commissioned and underway. This project has been delayed to avoid community consultation processes conflicting with development of the Community Strategic Plan and Disability Inclusion Action Plan. The draft Sport and Recreation Plan is expected by end April 2017. ','3','OC6.12.10'),(0000000728,NULL,'16/17',01,100,'All cemeteries surveyed to allow analysis of available land and supply. All cemeteries have capacity for five (5) years minimum. ','4','LA3.22.1');
